<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="488" pageId="1" pageNumber="484" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,942,1293]" pageId="1" pageNumber="484">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1230,1256]" pageId="1" pageNumber="484">Description.</emphasis>
Length. 0.9–1.2 mm. Body plump. Pigmentation uniformly bright red when alive and in ethanol (
<figureCitation box="[160,225,1267,1293]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1773,1797]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,1317,1749]" captionTargetId="figure-272@1.[151,1436,1317,1749]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Setanodosa, habitus in ethanol. A, a reddish undescribed species from Sutherland, Northern Cape, South Africa; B, Setanodosa jacquesi sp. nov. Scales: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6651285" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6651285/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="484">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6651285" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6651285" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6651285/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="484" startId="1.[151,250,1773,1797]" targetBox="[151,1436,1317,1749]" targetPageId="1">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1773,1833]" pageId="1" pageNumber="484">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,268,1773,1797]" pageId="1" pageNumber="484">FIGURE 1</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Salmon" authorityYear="1942" box="[280,397,1773,1797]" class="Collembola" family="Brachystomellidae" genus="Setanodosa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poduromorpha" pageId="1" pageNumber="484" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[280,397,1773,1797]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="484">Setanodosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, habitus in ethanol. A, a reddish undescribed species from Sutherland, Northern Cape, South Africa; B, 
<taxonomicName authority="Janion-Scheepers &amp; Deharveng, 2022" authorityName="Janion-Scheepers &amp; Deharveng" authorityYear="2022" box="[151,358,1809,1833]" class="Collembola" family="Brachystomellidae" genus="Setanodosa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poduromorpha" pageId="1" pageNumber="484" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jacquesi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[151,358,1809,1833]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="484">Setanodosa jacquesi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[365,446,1809,1833]" pageId="1" pageNumber="484">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[365,446,1809,1833]" pageId="1" pageNumber="484" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
Scales: 0.5 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1879,2014]" pageId="1" pageNumber="484">Granulation fine and regular. Diameter of a granule same as socket of the tergite S-chaetae. Paurochaetotic and moderately heterochaetotic.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1879,2014]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1436,151,393]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="485" pageId="1" pageNumber="484">
Antennae (
<figureCitation box="[322,395,1951,1977]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1362,1386]" captionTargetBox="[349,1242,424,1334]" captionTargetId="figure-120@2.[338,1248,417,1339]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Setanodosa jacquesi sp. nov. Antenna, dorsal side of segments III and IV. Scale: 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6651287" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6651287/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="484">Figs 2</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[408,446,1951,1977]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1998,2022]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,1410,1974]" captionTargetId="figure-141@2.[152,1436,1410,1974]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 3. Setanodosa jacquesi sp. nov. A, Apical bulb of Ant. IV; B, ocelli; C, PAO and external ocelli. Scales: 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6651289" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6651289/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="484">3A</figureCitation>
). Antennae short, about 3/4 as long as head. Ant. I, II and III with 7, 12 and 17/18 ordinary chaetae respectively, some very slightly serrated. Ant. III and IV fused dorsally with clear ventral separation. Sensory organ on third antennal segment complete, with two small internal globular S-chaetae surrounded by two tapering, blunt, subequal guard S-chaetae, and a ventral S-microchaeta. Ant. IV dorsally with long ordinary and mou-chaetae, of very similar morphology, thin, and hardly blunt apically; S-chaetae undistinguishable, possibly corresponding to the shortest dorsal chaetae; a small dorso-external thick S-microchaeta distally. Subapical organite “or” extremely minute. Apical bulb very large, irregular, trilobed. Ventral sensory rasp not differentiated.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,151,393]" pageId="2" pageNumber="485">
Ocular plate (
<figureCitation box="[352,473,331,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1998,2022]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,1410,1974]" captionTargetId="figure-141@2.[152,1436,1410,1974]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 3. Setanodosa jacquesi sp. nov. A, Apical bulb of Ant. IV; B, ocelli; C, PAO and external ocelli. Scales: 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6651289" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6651289/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="485">Fig. 3B, C</figureCitation>
). Ocelli 8 + 8, in black pigmented eyepatch. PAO round with 6-8 vesicles, arranged in a circle, approximately the same size as an ocellus.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6651287" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6651287" box="[151,1175,1362,1387]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6651287/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="485" startId="2.[151,250,1362,1386]" targetBox="[349,1242,424,1334]" targetPageId="2">
