<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,151,609]" pageId="3" pageNumber="486">
Mouthparts (
<figureCitation box="[343,463,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1970,1994]" captionTargetBox="[298,1298,647,1937]" captionTargetId="figure-238@3.[289,1298,633,1947]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 4. Setanodosa jacquesi sp. nov. A, maxilla; B, labium; C, dorsal chaetotaxy of head (x, chaeta absent asymmetrically). Scales: A, 10 µm; B, 20 µm; C, 50 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6651291" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6651291/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="486">Fig. 4A, B</figureCitation>
). Buccal cone truncated. Mandibles absent. Maxilla head typical of the genus, globular, with five strong, apically rounded teeth and parallel striations proximally, a sixth one, very reduced, sometimes present basally. Labium with subequal chaetae.A, B, C, D, E, F, f, G and 5 lateral ones (a, b, c, d, e); rooted papillate chaeta L present; no x-papilla seen.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,151,609]" pageId="3" pageNumber="486">
Dorsal chaetotaxy (
<figureCitation box="[420,514,295,321]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1970,1994]" captionTargetBox="[298,1298,647,1937]" captionTargetId="figure-238@3.[289,1298,633,1947]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 4. Setanodosa jacquesi sp. nov. A, maxilla; B, labium; C, dorsal chaetotaxy of head (x, chaeta absent asymmetrically). Scales: A, 10 µm; B, 20 µm; C, 50 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6651291" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6651291/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="486">Figs 4C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[527,632,294,321]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1232,1256]" captionTargetBox="[218,1369,181,1209]" captionTargetId="figure-18@4.[218,1369,181,1209]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 5. Setanodosa jacquesi sp. nov. A, Dorso-external S-chaeta of Th. II; B, Dorso-internal macrochaeta of Abd. VI; C, Dorso-external (De) and dorso-lateral (DL) chaetal groups of Abd. I; D, furcal area; E, female genital plate. Scales. A,B,C, 10 µm; D,E, 20 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6651293" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6651293/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="486">5A, B, C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[645,661,295,322]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1969,1993]" captionTargetBox="[205,1377,1362,1936]" captionTargetId="figure-65@4.[200,1386,1353,1946]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 6. Setanodosa jacquesi sp. nov. Tergite chaetotaxy. A, Th. I-III; B, Abd. II-VI (x, chaetae absent asymmetrically). Scale: 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6651295" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6651295/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="486">6</figureCitation>
). Dorsal macrochaetae of moderate length, straight, thick, sheathed, smooth, and slightly clavate on Abd. III to VI. Mesochaetae curved, non-sheathed, not clavate, smooth or slightly serrated. S-chaetae thinner, rather short, subequal, 0.45 as long as dorso-external macrochaetae on Abd. V. Chaetotaxy of head with asymmetries, chaetae a0 and an uneven chaeta at the level of d2 present. Th. II to Abd. V macrochaetae as 22/22223 per side. Th. I to Abd. V dorso-internal chaetae as 143/33332. Th. II to Abd. V S-chaetae as 2,2/2,1,1,1,1 per side, ms present laterally on Th. II, remote from S-chaeta. Position of S-chaetae 3,3/4,4,4,4,2. Thorax I with 3 + 3 chaetae. Th. II with (9+2S+ms) and Th. III with (8+2S) per side, chaetae a2 absent on Th. III. Abd. VI with 6 clavate chaetae and 7 or 8 acuminate chaetae, of which one anterior (a0) and one posterior (p0?) are unpaired.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6651291" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6651291" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6651291/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="486" startId="3.[151,250,1970,1994]" targetBox="[298,1298,647,1937]" targetPageId="3">
