<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,150,537]" pageId="5" pageNumber="488">
Ventral chaetotaxy (
<figureCitation box="[425,550,150,177]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1232,1256]" captionTargetBox="[218,1369,181,1209]" captionTargetId="figure-18@4.[218,1369,181,1209]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 5. Setanodosa jacquesi sp. nov. A, Dorso-external S-chaeta of Th. II; B, Dorso-internal macrochaeta of Abd. VI; C, Dorso-external (De) and dorso-lateral (DL) chaetal groups of Abd. I; D, furcal area; E, female genital plate. Scales. A,B,C, 10 µm; D,E, 20 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6651293" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6651293/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="488">Figs 5D, E</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[563,599,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1424,1448]" captionTargetBox="[168,1431,573,1393]" captionTargetId="figure-208@5.[154,1432,561,1401]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 7. Setanodosa jacquesi sp. nov. A, Tibiotarsus of leg III; B, Ventral chaetotaxy of abdomen (Abd. IV: Ve group with a duplicated chaeta posteriorly). Scales: A, 20 µm; B, 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6651297" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6651297/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="488">7B</figureCitation>
). Chaetae smooth, thin and acuminate. Thoracic sternites without chaetae. Ventral tube with 2+2 distal and 1+1 postero-basal chaetae. Abd. II with 2+2 chaetae Ve, Abd. III with 6–7+6–7 chaetae Ve, Abd. IV with 6–7+6–7 chaetae VL and 7–8+7–8 chaetae Ve (with rare asymmetries). Furca and tenaculum absent, furcal rest with 4 microchaetae (
<figureCitation box="[642,730,258,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1232,1256]" captionTargetBox="[218,1369,181,1209]" captionTargetId="figure-18@4.[218,1369,181,1209]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 5. Setanodosa jacquesi sp. nov. A, Dorso-external S-chaeta of Th. II; B, Dorso-internal macrochaeta of Abd. VI; C, Dorso-external (De) and dorso-lateral (DL) chaetal groups of Abd. I; D, furcal area; E, female genital plate. Scales. A,B,C, 10 µm; D,E, 20 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6651293" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6651293/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="488">Fig. 5D</figureCitation>
). Abd. V with 2+2 chaetae Ag and 4–5+4–5 chaetae VL, genital plate of female with 13–17 circumgenital microchaetae and 1+1 or possibly 2+2 eugenital microchaetae (
<figureCitation box="[1341,1432,294,321]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1232,1256]" captionTargetBox="[218,1369,181,1209]" captionTargetId="figure-18@4.[218,1369,181,1209]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 5. Setanodosa jacquesi sp. nov. A, Dorso-external S-chaeta of Th. II; B, Dorso-internal macrochaeta of Abd. VI; C, Dorso-external (De) and dorso-lateral (DL) chaetal groups of Abd. I; D, furcal area; E, female genital plate. Scales. A,B,C, 10 µm; D,E, 20 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6651293" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6651293/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="488">Figs 5E</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[151,188,331,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1424,1448]" captionTargetBox="[168,1431,573,1393]" captionTargetId="figure-208@5.[154,1432,561,1401]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 7. Setanodosa jacquesi sp. nov. A, Tibiotarsus of leg III; B, Ventral chaetotaxy of abdomen (Abd. IV: Ve group with a duplicated chaeta posteriorly). Scales: A, 20 µm; B, 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6651297" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6651297/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="488">7B</figureCitation>
). Male genital plate not observed. Anal region with 3 hr chaetae on each valve and 14 + 14 Ve chaetae, of which 1-2 + 1-2 are macrochaetae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,150,537]" pageId="5" pageNumber="488">
Legs (
<figureCitation box="[271,363,403,429]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1424,1448]" captionTargetBox="[168,1431,573,1393]" captionTargetId="figure-208@5.[154,1432,561,1401]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 7. Setanodosa jacquesi sp. nov. A, Tibiotarsus of leg III; B, Ventral chaetotaxy of abdomen (Abd. IV: Ve group with a duplicated chaeta posteriorly). Scales: A, 20 µm; B, 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6651297" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6651297/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="488">Fig. 7A</figureCitation>
). Claw without internal or lateral tooth. Tibiotarsi I, II, III respectively with 19,19,18 chaetae (11,11,11 in the apical whorl and 8,8, 
<quantity box="[564,606,439,465]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.778" pageId="5" pageNumber="488" unit="in" value="7.0">7 in</quantity>
the basal whorl, chaetae M present); among them, 4,4,4 thick and strongly clavate chaetae (of which 2,2,2 dorsal and 2,2,2 ventral). Femur I, II, III with 12, 12, 11 chaetae; trochanter I, II, III with 6, 6, 6 chaetae; coxae I, II, III with 3, 6, 7 chaetae respectively.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
