<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="488" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1530,1881]" pageId="5" pageNumber="488">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,294,1530,1556]" pageId="5" pageNumber="488">Ecology</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Janion-Scheepers &amp; Deharveng, 2022" authorityName="Janion-Scheepers &amp; Deharveng" authorityYear="2022" box="[308,537,1530,1556]" class="Collembola" family="Brachystomellidae" genus="Setanodosa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poduromorpha" pageId="5" pageNumber="488" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jacquesi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[308,537,1530,1556]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="488">Setanodosa jacquesi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[544,634,1530,1556]" pageId="5" pageNumber="488">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[544,634,1530,1556]" pageId="5" pageNumber="488" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is only know from a single location in the 
<collectingRegion box="[1114,1254,1530,1556]" country="South Africa" name="Western Cape" pageId="5" pageNumber="488">Cape region</collectingRegion>
. It has been collected floating on water in a rock pool.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="488" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1530,1881]" box="[199,1009,1602,1629]" pageId="5" pageNumber="488">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,328,1602,1628]" pageId="5" pageNumber="488">Etymology</emphasis>
. We dedicate this species to its collector, Jacques Scheepers.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1530,1881]" pageId="5" pageNumber="488">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,408,1638,1664]" pageId="5" pageNumber="488">Barcoding results</emphasis>
. The mitochondrial genome of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Schaffer" baseAuthorityYear="1896" box="[756,1025,1638,1664]" class="Collembola" family="Brachystomellidae" genus="Brachystomella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poduromorpha" pageId="5" pageNumber="488" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="parvula">
<emphasis box="[756,1025,1638,1664]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="488">Brachystomella parvula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been recently published by 
<bibRefCitation author="Jiang, L. &amp; Dong, J. &amp; Jin, J. &amp; Zhang, F." pageId="5" pageNumber="488" pagination="104 - 105" refId="ref6318" refString="Jiang, L., Dong, J., Jin, J. &amp; Zhang, F. (2019) Mitochondrial genome of Brachystomella parvula (Collembola: Brachystomellidae). Mitochondrial DNA Part B Resources, 5 (1), 104 - 105. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 23802359.2019.1698372" type="journal article" year="2019">
Jiang 
<emphasis box="[151,202,1674,1700]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="488">et al</emphasis>
. (2019)
</bibRefCitation>
. We give here the first COI sequences published for different genera, species and populations of the family, including two 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Salmon" authorityYear="1942" box="[405,534,1710,1736]" class="Collembola" family="Brachystomellidae" genus="Setanodosa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poduromorpha" pageId="5" pageNumber="488" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[405,534,1710,1736]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="488">Setanodosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and two 
<taxonomicName box="[645,1061,1710,1737]" pageId="5" pageNumber="488">
<emphasis box="[645,821,1710,1736]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="488">Brachystomella</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Agren, H." box="[828,970,1710,1737]" pageId="5" pageNumber="488" pagination="113 - 176" refId="ref5821" refString="Agren, H. (1903) Zur Kenntniss der Apterygoten-Fauna Sud-Schwedens. Stettiner Entomologische Zeitung, 64, 113 - 176." type="journal article" year="1903">Agren, 1903</bibRefCitation>
species
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1078,1149,1710,1736]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1921,1945]" captionTargetBox="[172,1420,194,1880]" captionTargetId="figure-18@6.[155,1433,181,1897]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 8. Neighbor-joining K2P distance tree for COI of some Brachystomella and Setanodosa species (see Table 1 for locations)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6651299" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6651299/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="488">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
). Between-species divergences are high, ranging from 22 to 26 %, i.e. similar to or even higher than between-species divergences observed in other families according to available literature (
<bibRefCitation author="Porco, D. &amp; Bedos, A. &amp; Greenslade, P. &amp; Janion, C. &amp; Skarzynski, D. &amp; Stevens, M. I. &amp; Deharveng, L." box="[719,919,1782,1809]" pageId="5" pageNumber="488" pagination="470 - 477" refId="ref6580" refString="Porco, D., Bedos, A., Greenslade, P., Janion, C., Skarzynski, D., Stevens, M. I. &amp; Deharveng, L. (2012) Challenging species delimitation in Collembola: cryptic diversity among common springtails unveiled by DNA barcoding. Invertebrate Systematics, 26 (6), 470 - 477. https: // doi. org / 10.1071 / IS 12026" type="journal article" year="2012">
Porco 
<emphasis box="[794,845,1782,1808]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="488">et al</emphasis>
. 2012
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Sun, X. &amp; Bedos, A. &amp; Deharveng, L." box="[931,1109,1782,1809]" pageId="5" pageNumber="488" pagination="5021" refId="ref6829" refString="Sun, X., Bedos, A. &amp; Deharveng, L. (2018) Unusually low genetic divergence at COI barcode locus between two species of intertidal Thalassaphorura (Collembola: Onychiuridae). PeerJ, 6, e 5021. https: // doi. org / 10.7717 / peerj. 5021" type="journal article" year="2018">
Sun 
<emphasis box="[983,1033,1782,1808]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="488">et al</emphasis>
. 2018
</bibRefCitation>
). Divergences within species are low (0-1.8 %). As expected, 
<taxonomicName authority="Janion-Scheepers &amp; Deharveng, 2022" authorityName="Janion-Scheepers &amp; Deharveng" authorityYear="2022" box="[510,631,1819,1845]" class="Collembola" family="Brachystomellidae" genus="Setanodosa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poduromorpha" pageId="5" pageNumber="488" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jacquesi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[510,631,1819,1845]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="488">S. jacquesi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[638,727,1818,1844]" pageId="5" pageNumber="488">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[638,727,1818,1844]" pageId="5" pageNumber="488" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is well separated from the sub-Antarctic species 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Schaffer" baseAuthorityYear="1891" box="[1274,1388,1819,1845]" class="Collembola" family="Brachystomellidae" genus="Setanodosa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poduromorpha" pageId="5" pageNumber="488" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="steineni">
<emphasis box="[1274,1388,1819,1845]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="488">S. steineni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the only other species of the genus which has been barcoded so far.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
